class Solution {
    public void duplicateZeros(int[] arr) {
        // Clone the current array as the source of inputs.
        int[] original = arr.clone();

        // Create two different counter, one for the original array
        // the other for the modified array.
        int cO = 0;
        int cA = 0;

        // Continue until the modified array counter
        // is equal to the length of array.
        while (cA < arr.length) {
            // Copy the current index of original array
            // to the current modified array.
            arr[cA] = original[cO];
            cA++;

            // Only if the current counter of array is still less than the modified array
            // and if the original counter points to a zero.
            if (cA < arr.length && original[cO] == 0) {
                arr[cA] = 0;
                cA++;
            }
            cO++;
        }
    }
}
```

