Ideas:
* Hold values from the original array in a queue and pop elements one by one
* If a 0 is at the front of the queue when popping, place it in the array twice
* This technique can easily be modified for placing zeros 3 times or 4 times or etc. Most of the two pointer 
solutions here would require significant changes. Most interviews have follow up questions/requirements so make robust solutions!
```
class Solution {
    public void duplicateZeros(int[] arr) {
        Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();
        for(int i : arr) queue.add(i);
        int i = 0;
        while(i <= arr.length - 1) {
            int top = queue.poll();
            if(top != 0) {
                arr[i++] = top;
            } else {
                arr[i++] = top;
                if(i > arr.length - 1) return;
                arr[i++] = top;
            }
        }
    }
}
```

